<div class=3D"row">
  <h2>Description, how many faces, edges and vertices are there in an icosa=
hedron</h2>
  <p>
 =20
     =20
      <b>The icosahedron</b>, (icosa =3D 20 and hedron =3D Face) has <b>20 =
faces</b> where each of these faces is an equilateral triangle, has <b>30 e=
dges and 12 vertices</b>. At each of the vertices, 5 edges meet.
      =20
      </p> =20
</div>

  <div class=3D"row">
    <h2>Examples of an icosahedron</h2>
    <p>
   =20
     =20
      We can find many <b>objects that look like an icosahedron</b>, exampl=
es of icosahedron shaped objects are: 20-sided dice that are used in some b=
oard games. Some viruses that affect health are icosahedron, one of them is=
 the human papilloma virus.
      <br><br>
      Another famous object that could be considered an icosahedron are soc=
cer balls, but they are actually truncated icosahedra, they have a cut on i=
ts surface creating 12 pentagons and 20 hexagons. Can you think of any othe=
r examples? leave a comment in the comment section at the bottom of the pag=
e.
      =20
        </p>=20
  </div>


<div class=3D"row">
  <h2>Formula for the volume of an icosahedron</h2>
  <p>
 =20
     =20
      To <b>calculate the volume of a icosahedron</b> you can calculate the=
 volume of 20 equal triangular pyramids joint by their vertex. The difficul=
ty is being able to calculate the height of these pyramids, but we can make=
 use of the following formula, where we only need the value of an edge. You=
 can also use the online calculator to <b>calculate the volume of the icosa=
hedron automatically</b>.
      =20
      </p>=20
  <div style=3D"display:inline-block;width:auto;vertical-align:middle;text-=
align:center;" class=3D"smallformula">
      <div style=3D"display:inline-block;width:auto;vertical-align:middle;"=
>
        <span>Volume =3D</span>
      </div>
      <div style=3D"display:inline-block;width:auto;vertical-align:middle;"=
